name: Alive
definition: Showing characteristics of life; displaying signs of life.

name: Dead
definition: The cessation of life.

name: Opted-out
definition: A grantor's dissent to the terms of agreement offered by a grantee without an opportunity for to assent to any terms.

name: Follow-Up Completed
definition: The follow-up protocols were completed.

name: Lost To Follow-Up
definition: The loss or lack of continuation of subject participation after a study has officially closed.

name: Never Dosed
definition: An indication that a subject has not ever been dosed with the study treatment or investigational product.

name: Permanent Intervention Discontinuation due to Adverse Event, Subject Continues Follow Up
Permanent Intervention Discontinuation, No Subject Follow Up
Permanent Intervention Discontinuation, Subject Continues Follow Up
Screening Not Completed
definition: An indication that recruitment was closed before the subject could be randomized.

name: Study Subject Not Enrolled
definition: The study subject is/was not enrolled.

name: Subject Entered Additional Research Study
definition: The study subject has been enrolled in an additional research study.

name: Subject Lost to Follow Up
definition: The subject was not available for follow-up procedures.

name: Subject Not Assigned to Arm
definition: The subject, who met eligibility criteria, was not assigned to an arm and was not treated.

name: Subject Off Trial due to Death
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject is currently off the trial because they are deceased.

name: Subject Off Trial due to Expired Biopsy
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject is currently off the trial because of an expired biopsy.

name: Subject Off Trial due to Lack of Consent
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject is currently off the trial because they have not granted or received consent.

name: Subject Off Trial due to No Available Treatment Arm
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject is currently off the trial because they do not fill the criteria for inclusion into an existing treatment arm.

name: Subject Off Trial due to Registration Error
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject is currently off the trial because of an error that occurred during the registration process.

name: Subject Off Trial Following Assignment to Protocol Treatment Arm due to Death
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject that was assigned to a protocol treatment arm is currently off the trial because they are deceased.

name: Subject Off Trial Following Assignment to Protocol Treatment Arm due to Disease Progression
definition: A status indicating that a clinical trial subject that was assigned to a protocol treatment arm is currently off the trial because they have experienced disease progression.

name: Subject Received Unplanned Treatment
definition: The subject, who met eligibility criteria, was assigned to an arm but received treatment not associated with any of the planned arms.

name: Subject Removed at Sponsor Request
definition: An indication that the study subject was removed from the study at the sponsor's request.
